# PATCH 009: Copilot anti-fingerprinting and persistent conversation-warm initiator mix
#
# Reduces account ban risk by making proxy traffic look like real VS Code usage:
#
# 1. Per-account header diversity: Deterministically selects User-Agent,
#    Editor-Version, and Editor-Plugin-Version from realistic version pools
#    based on a hash of the API token. Each account gets a consistent but
#    unique fingerprint.
#
# 2. Persistent session metadata: VScode-MachineId is derived deterministically
#    from the API token (stable forever, like a real hardware fingerprint).
#    VScode-SessionId rotates every 4 hours (simulating editor restarts)
#    instead of generating a new random UUID per request.
#
# 3. Conversation-aware X-Initiator: First-seen conversation roots bill as
#    "user", explicit tool loops and previous_response_id continuations stay
#    "agent", warmed conversations flip back to "agent", and 2% of warmed
#    follow-ups still use the real initiator for extra noise.
#
# 4. Persistent warm conversation cache: Stores hashed warm-root expiry state
#    under the auth dir so watchtower/deploy restarts do not reset every active
#    conversation back to a billed cold start.
#
diff --git a/internal/runtime/executor/github_copilot_executor.go b/internal/runtime/executor/github_copilot_executor.go
